&lt;p&gt;Doctor&#39;s Assistant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Surgical Assessment Unit (SAU) is increasing the doctor’s assistant (DA) team. This is in recognition of the expanding service need within acute surgery admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of an SAU DA is desirable, interesting &amp; fast paced working in conjunction with 6 various surgical teams (colorectal, HPB, OG, General, Vascular &amp; Urology).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SAU have approx. 40 -50 acute referrals daily and many patients will be assessed in the large triage area. We boast our own scanning suite, 2 examination rooms, 22 inpatient beds with adjoining wards for transfer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any interested applicants are encouraged to meet Sister Andrews on SAU for a walk around to fully appreciate the pathways of our surgical patients however early application is advisable as the post is likely to close due to a high volume of interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To contact Sister Andrews please use the following: sianandrews@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively (01752) 432733&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
